<tr>
<td class=3D"body-header-container" style=3D"border-collapse: collapse; mso=
-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt;">
<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Bank M&amp;A</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One conclusion that a lot of people ha=
ve drawn from the 2023 crisis of US regional banks is that the US has <a hr=
ef=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/31994559.257406/aHR0cHM=
6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDYtMTQvcmVnaW9uYW=
wtYmFua3MtZG9uLXQtZmVlbC1sb3ZlZD9jbXBpZD1CQkQwNzA1MjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fb=
WVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMzA3MDUmdXRtX2Nh=
bXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB18b5ac1f" itemprop=3D"Stor=
yLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; t=
ext-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-co=
lor: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">way too =
many</a> regional banks. There are more than 4,000 banks, which creates a l=
ot of work for bank supervisors, and which means that it=E2=80=99s hard for=
 depositors to be sure that their bank is safe. When depositors get nervous=
, they run to household-name too-big-to-fail banks, leaving the other, you =
know, 3,990 banks vulnerable.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One obvious s=
olution to this problem is to turn those 4,000 banks into, say, 2,000 banks=
, or maybe 20 banks. That would make life easier for regulators and supervi=
sors =E2=80=94=C2=A0fewer banks to keep track of =E2=80=94=C2=A0and also ma=
ke each individual bank a bit bigger and more diversified and hopefully mor=
e robust.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One thing that means is that it=
=E2=80=99s a great time to be a financial-institutions mergers-and-acquisit=
ions banker? The <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/3=
1994559.257406/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9hcnRpY2xlcy9iYW5rLWRlYWxzLWFyZS1i=
YWNrLW9uLXRoZS10YWJsZS1nZXR0aW5nLW9uZS1kb25lLWNvdWxkLWJlLW1lc3N5LTNkNzdhMmI=
yP21vZD1ocF9sZWFkX3BvczU/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB621d01a4" itemprop=3D"Sto=
ryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; =
text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-c=
olor: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">Wall St=
reet Journal reports</a>:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The i=
ndustry is poised to consolidate at a pace unseen in years. If July=E2=80=
=99s earning announcements revive fears of fleeing depositors, the push to =
merge may turn urgent. Treasury Secretary Janet Yellen predicted that highe=
r rates may lead to more deals; and bank regulators are signaling they are =
open to them.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CWe certainly don=E2=
=80=99t want overconcentration and we=E2=80=99re pro-competition, but that =
doesn=E2=80=99t mean no,=E2=80=9D Yellen said about mergers.=C2=A0</p><p st=
yle=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Peter Orszag, the former Obama administration offic=
ial and incoming CEO of Lazard has privately urged Yellen and her staff to =
pave the way for more bank deals, people familiar with the matter said.</p>=
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There are more than 4,000 U.S. banks, and many=
 are staring at eye-watering technology and regulatory costs. Those expense=
s, along with today=E2=80=99s headaches such as fickle depositors and shaky=
 real-estate loans, threaten to squeeze the industry=E2=80=99s profits.=C2=
=A0=E2=80=A6</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Regulators have privately expr=
essed a general willingness to include mergers as part of the solution to i=
nstability in the banking system, people familiar with the matter said.=C2=
=A0</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If the 4,000 banks should =
be 2,000 banks, that means there need to be about 2,000 bank mergers? I sus=
pect that if Janet Yellen could snap her fingers and reduce the 4,000 US ba=
nks to 2,000, she=E2=80=99d do it. And if Peter Orszag could get mandated o=
n a small fraction of those 2,000 bank deals that=E2=80=99s a nice year for=
 his financial institutions group.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I suppos=
e a lot of those deals will be pretty small and not that lucrative for thei=
r advisers, but on the other hand my impression is that bank M&amp;A is =E2=
=80=A6=C2=A0I don=E2=80=99t want to say that it=E2=80=99s easy, exactly, bu=
t bank mergers have a tendency to happen over the course of a weekend, so y=
ou can do a lot of them pretty efficiently. It=E2=80=99s not so much a long=
 courtship and a quest for cultural fit, it=E2=80=99s more like opening a d=
ata room on Friday and saying =E2=80=9Chey we gotta announce a deal before =
the open Monday.=E2=80=9D You invite in 20 bidders, you pick the top bid, y=
ou tell the other 19 =E2=80=9Csorry it didn=E2=80=99t work out but we=E2=80=
=99ll have three more of these next Friday.=E2=80=9D If there are 2,000 ban=
k deals coming, you can kind of set up an assembly line.=C2=A0</p><p style=
=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The other nice thing about this business, for an inves=
tment bank, is that it is sort of countercyclical. Higher interest rates ar=
e bad for, say, private-equity leveraged buyouts, but they are good for <a =
href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/31994559.257406/aHR0c=
HM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9hcnRpY2xlcy9yZWJvdW5kLWluLXJhdGVzLXB1dHMtcHJlc3N1cmUt=
b24tYmFua3MtYWZmZjBjMDA_bW9kPWhwX2xlYWRfcG9zMg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB370=
857fc" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" sty=
le=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width=
: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background=
-color: #ccc;">making regional banks nervous</a>. As rates go up, M&amp;A w=
ill be quiet in a lot of sectors, but it might get busier in banking.</p><p=
 style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">By the way, one way to tell this story goes some=
thing like this:</p><ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40=
px; margin: 16px 0;">=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Traditionally, wh=
en the Fed raised interest rates, banks did not really raise the rates they=
 paid on deposits all that much. The =E2=80=9C<a href=3D"https://link.mail.=
bloombergbusiness.com/click/31994559.257406/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmN=
vbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDUtMDkvaXQtcy1uZXZlci10b28tbGF0ZS1mb3ItYm=
Fua3MtdG8taGVkZ2U_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDcwNTIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpb=
CZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMwNzA1JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25l=
eXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBbc5e17f8" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscop=
e=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration:=
 none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; b=
order-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">deposit beta</a>=E2=80=
=9D was low, because for various reasons (relationship strength, local mono=
polies, regulation) banks did not really need to compete with each other on=
 rates to attract depositors.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">In t=
he current hiking cycle, however, regional banks=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://li=
nk.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/31994559.257406/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21=
iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDUtMDQvbm9ib2R5LXRydXN0cy10aGUtYm=
Fua3Mtbm93P2NtcGlkPUJCRDA3MDUyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX=
3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMDcwNSZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVm=
Zg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB93bce82b" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"i=
temscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none =
!important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-=
bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"><em>do=C2=A0</em>need to pay =
competitive interest rates</a> to keep deposits, and as rates go up they ha=
ve to pay up a lot and don=E2=80=99t make any money.</li>=09<li style=3D"ma=
rgin-bottom: 5px;">The solution is to merge banks to reduce competition so =
they don=E2=80=99t have to pay competitive interest rates so they can keep =
making money.</li></ol><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I don=E2=80=99t think a=
nyone would put the story quite that way, and you can understand why. (=E2=
=80=9CWe=E2=80=99re pro-competition,=E2=80=9D says Yellen, and no banking o=
r antitrust regulator is going to go around saying =E2=80=9Cthere needs to =
be less banking competition so depositors don=E2=80=99t get paid market int=
erest rates so banks can keep making money.=E2=80=9D) But I think it=E2=80=
=99s true? The basic problem in banking is that competition is good but fin=
ancial stability is also good, and they are kind of at odds with each other=
.</p><table class=3D"liveintent-sponsored-content" width=3D"auto" cellpaddi=
ng=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0">
