<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Weird CEO pay</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CMeet the CEOs Who Pull In Mor=
e Than $100 Million a Year,=E2=80=9D says <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloo=
mbergbusiness.com/click/31994559.257406/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9hcnRpY2x=
lcy9tZWV0LXRoZS1jZW9zLXdoby1wdWxsLWluLW1vcmUtdGhhbi0xMDAtbWlsbGlvbi1hLXllYX=
ItODQwOWFmZTA_bW9kPWhwX2xpc3RiX3BvczU/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB36ab06f4" it=
emprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"col=
or: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; bo=
rder-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #=
ccc;"> this Wall Street Journal headline</a>, but that=E2=80=99s not quite =
right:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The chief executives of =
Hertz, Peloton and Pinterest all earned more than $100 million in 2022, top=
ping almost every CEO in the S&amp;P 500 including Apple=E2=80=99s Tim Cook=
, who made $99 million. Also on that list: The man who runs CS Disco, a clo=
ud-services provider that caters to attorneys and has a market capitalizati=
on of about $500 million.=C2=A0</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;=
">Sure okay the CS Disco guy =E2=80=9Creceived $500,000 in salary plus stoc=
k options valued at $109 million=E2=80=9D in 2022, but he =E2=80=9Cearned j=
ust under $1 million total in 2021, the year the company went public in lat=
e July.=E2=80=9D So he pulls in $55 million a year, on average, over the la=
st two years, not =E2=80=9Cmore than $100 million a year.=E2=80=9D But that=
 $109 million 2022 options grant is not an annual occurrence; that=E2=80=99=
s meant to tide him over for a while. =E2=80=9CWe believe that an up-front,=
 long-term option grant with performance-based vesting would be most motiva=
ting to Mr. Camara and would have a greater impact than an annual long-term=
 incentive award,=E2=80=9D <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.c=
om/click/31994559.257406/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYX=
RhLzE2MjU2NDEvMDAwMTE5MzEyNTIyMTY0MDczL2Q2NjMwNzdkZGVmMTRhLmh0bSN0eDY2MzA3N=
182/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB5181e3b9" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"=
itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none=
 !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border=
-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> said the company</a> in 202=
2, when it asked shareholders to approve the grant. Getting a $109 million =
one-time equity award is not the same as earning $100 million a year.</p><p=
 style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Also it=E2=80=99s not real money: The $109 milli=
on is the calculated fair value of the options grant at the time it was awa=
rded, but it consists of a bunch of options to buy stock at a strike price =
of $32 per share, and they only vest in tranches if the stock reaches a ser=
ies of milestone prices starting at $150 per share and going up to $900. Th=
e stock closed Monday at $8.40 per share. If he gets the stock to $900 per =
share, then the package will be worth something like $3.8 billion to him, b=
ut on the other hand at $900 per share this will be a $50 billion company a=
nd he=E2=80=99ll be worth it. But the <em>most likely </em>value of this $1=
09 million pay package is zero dollars.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0=
;">Not all of the examples are like this, but a lot are:</p><blockquote><p =
style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">At Hertz, Stephen Scherr=E2=80=99s total pay of $=
182 million included $3.4 million in salary and bonus. A further $178 milli=
on in restricted stock is structured to vest through 2026, much of it only =
if the company=E2=80=99s shares reach 90-day average price targets ranging =
up to nearly double its current share price.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;=
">In its annual proxy statement, Hertz said two price targets had already b=
een met, meaning about $50 million in shares at recent prices stand to vest=
